notes: 1st ever official ODI between two ICC Associate teams.
Match was originally scheduled to be a day/night match.

SF Dukanwala 10-0-29-5, 7th best bowling for any team in World Cup matches, best ever bowling by an ICC Associate player in official ODIs (previous best: 4-21 by EA Brandes, ZIM v ENG at Albury 18/03/1992), 1st 5-wicket-haul for UAE, 4th best ever ODI bowling in Pakistan (best ever by a non- Pakistani), best bowling by any player in Lahore.
Azhar Saeed and Saleem Raza 117 for the 1st wicket, 1st ever 100 partnership for any wicket for the UAE.
Saleem Raza 84, highest score for UAE in ODIs.
Mohammad Ishaq 51, 3rd highest ever score for UAE in ODIs, brought up his 50 with the winning runs.
1st ever win by the United Arab Emerites in official ODIs, 5th win by an ICC Associate in official ODIs.

milestones.description: Saleem Raza's 84 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for UAE), surpassing Mazhar Hussain's 70
Azhar Saeed has broken the record for most catches (2) in ODIs for UAE, going past Poonawala's 1
Azhar Saeed has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (7) for UAE, going past Arshad Laeeq
Cantrell and Aponso's 74-run partnership is NED's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 45 between Cantrell and Tim de Leede
Cantrell and Tim de Leede's 71-run partnership is NED's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 24 between Lubbers and Tim de Leede
Marcel Schewe and Bas Zuiderent's 9-run partnership is NED's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Klaas-Jan van Noortwijk and Bas Zuiderent
Azhar Saeed and Saleem Raza's 117-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 27 between Saleem Raza and Mylvaganam
Vijay Mehra and Mohammad Ishaq's 82-run partnership is UAE's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 41 between Mazhar Hussain and Mohammad Ishaq
Saleem Raza has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (6) in ODIs for UAE, going past Arshad Laeeq's 2
Saleem Raza has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (64) in an innings in ODIs for UAE, going past Vijay Mehra's 24
Azhar Saeed and Saleem Raza's 117-run partnership is UAE's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 94 between Vijay Mehra and Mazhar Hussain
Nolan Clarke has broken the record for most ducks (2) in ODIs for NED, going past Tim de Leede's 1
Saleem Raza has broken the record for most sixes (8) in ODIs for UAE, going past Arshad Laeeq's 2
Azhar Saeed has become the top wicket-taker for UAE in ODIs with 6 wickets, going past Johanne Samarasekera's 4
Nolan Clarke has broken the record for most catches (3) in ODIs for NED, going past Bas Zuiderent's 2
Aponso has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for NED, going past Bakker
